test_most_justification: Only partially met for some Python modules.

warnings_justification: Python code is checked with pylint. All Python code runs with PYTHONWARNINGS=error or at least PYTHONWARNINGS=all to immediately indicate issues because of deprecated Python features.
know_secure_design_justification: Michael Ströder is the initiator of the project and thus familiar with the whole code base.
know_common_errors_justification: For web applications OWASP guide-lines are followed. For the OpenLDAP configuration the main goal of the project is to strictly follow need to know and least privilege principles. Michael Ströder has 20 years of experience setting up OpenLDAP with strict access control.
crypto_published_justification:
https://code.stroeder.com/AE-DIR/ansible-ae-dir-server/src/branch/master/defaults/main.yml
Relevant ansible variables: openldap_tls_cipher_suite, openldap_tls_protocol_min, apache_ssl_protocol, apache_ssl_cipher_suite
crypto_call_justification: Underlying cryptographic libraries (e.g. OpenSSL) are used either by OpenLDAP, Apache directly or via Python module package cryptography.
crypto_floss_justification:
All the software components used are FLOSS:
Underlying cryptographic libraries (e.g. OpenSSL) are used either by OpenLDAP, Apache directly or via Python module package cryptography.
crypto_keylength_justification:
https://code.stroeder.com/AE-DIR/ansible-ae-dir-server/src/branch/master/defaults/main.yml
Relevant ansible variables: openldap_tls_cipher_suite, openldap_tls_protocol_min, apache_ssl_protocol, apache_ssl_cipher_suite
The default values are reviewed every six months.
crypto_password_storage_justification:
https://code.stroeder.com/AE-DIR/ansible-ae-dir-server/src/branch/master/defaults/main.yml
Relevant ansible variables: openldap_password_hash and openldap_password_crypt_salt_format
The crypt(3) scheme $6$rounds=20000$%.16s is used as default.
delivery_mitm_justification: Every network connection (mainly LDAP and HTTPS) uses TLS. There is even no mode to run without issuing TLS server certs.
vulnerabilities_fixed_60_days_justificat: There are no known vulnerabilities yet.
vulnerabilities_critical_fixed_justifica: There are no known vulnerabilities yet.
crypto_weaknesses_justification: This is met with one exception: The OATH standard uses HMAC algorithms based on SHA-1 which cannot be easily changed because of compability wit other existing implementations (see RFC 4226 and RFC 6238).
test_continuous_integration_justificatio: Only partially met for some Python modules (gitlab CI),
discussion_justification: https://code.stroeder.com/AE-DIR
no_leaked_credentials_justification: The aim of the whole design is to avoid the need to have private credentials in a public repo.

description: Open source render farm management software. An Academy Software Foundation project.
description_good_justification: The opencue.io homepage describes what OpenCue does and some of its features.
interact_justification: The opencue.io homepage contains a link to the "Getting Started" docs, which feature information on how to obtain OpenCue and links for filing GitHub issues. The homepage also contains a "Contribute" link, leading to our contributors guide.
contribution_justification: Non-trivial contribution file in repository: <https://github.com/imageworks/OpenCue/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md>.
contribution_requirements_justification: Project CONTRIBUTING file describes requirements for contributions: <https://github.com/imageworks/OpenCue/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md>

floss_license_osi_justification: The Apache-2.0 license is approved by the Open Source Initiative (OSI).
documentation_basics_justification: https://opencue.io/docs/
repo_public_justification: Repository on GitHub, which provides public git repositories with URLs.
repo_track_justification: Repository on GitHub, which uses git. git can track the changes, who made them, and when they were made.
repo_interim_justification: GitHub pull requests and branches satisfy this requirement.
repo_distributed_justification: Repository on GitHub, which uses git. git is distributed.
version_unique_justification: Every release is tagged with a Major.Minor.Patch version number. The version number is deterministic, in that every commit to master is identifiable by a version number, regardless of whether it has been officially released or not.
version_tags_justification: Release versions are provided as git tags.
release_notes_justification: Release notes are provided on our GitHub releases page: <https://github.com/imageworks/OpenCue/releases>
release_notes_vulns_justification: There have been no publicly known vulnerabilities at this time.
report_tracker_justification: The project uses the GitHub issue tracker: <https://github.com/imageworks/OpenCue/issues>
report_process_justification:
Users may file bugs using our bug report template: <https://github.com/imageworks/OpenCue/issues/new?labels=bug&template=bug_report.md>
Or, general issue filing at <https://github.com/imageworks/OpenCue/issues>
report_responses_justification: Bug issues are regularly triaged by project leads, and either fixed or added to a backlog as necessary.
enhancement_responses_justification: Enhancement issues are regularly triaged by project leads, and either fixed or added to a backlog as necessary.
report_archive_justification: All past issues are available at <https://github.com/imageworks/OpenCue/issues>
vulnerability_report_process_justificati: The project security policy is published at https://github.com/AcademySoftwareFoundation/OpenCue/blob/master/SECURITY.md. This security policy appears when filing a new issue against the project.
vulnerability_report_response_justificat: No vulnerabilities have been reported yet, but regular issue triaging ensures they will be handled quickly.
build_justification: Java components use Gradle to build binaries. Python components use pip and setuptools for building and packaging Python components. GitHub Actions is used to automate this process.
build_common_tools_justification: Java components use Gradle to build binaries. Python components use pip and setuptools for building and packaging Python components.
build_floss_tools_justification: All tools in our build stack are OSS.
test_justification: Java components use JUnit and Gradle for running tests. Python components use the unittest module setuptools for running tests. Test execution is automated via our CI system using GitHub Actions.
test_most_justification: Coverage for the project is >50%, and the TSC is working to increase this over time. https://sonarcloud.io/dashboard?id=AcademySoftwareFoundation_OpenCue
test_policy_justification: Pull request templates document our policy of adding tests. Code reviewers are responsible for enforcing this policy. Sonar Quality Gate tracks our adherence to this policy.
tests_are_added_justification: Sonar Quality Gate tracks our adherence to this policy.
tests_documented_added_justification: Pull request templates document this policy.
warnings_justification: Java components use "-Xlint:all" and "-Werror" at build time. Python components use pylint, which is run as part of the testing suite. These tools must pass before pull requests can be merged. Sonar also identifies some additional warnings, these warnings have been addressed and our project has an "A" rating in Sonar.
warnings_fixed_justification: All warnings originally identified by the above tools have addressed in the master branch. The CI pipeline which runs on all pull requests ensures new warnings will not be created.
warnings_strict_justification: Warning tools use maximally strict settings. The only pylint checks which have been disabled deal with superficial coding style rules.
know_secure_design_justification: Existing TSC members have this knowledge.
know_common_errors_justification: Existing TSC members have this knowledge.
static_analysis_justification: SonarCloud is used to analyze code. The project currently maintains an "A" rating there. Analysis is run on every commit to master, and our release policy is to address any identified issues before a release can be produced.
static_analysis_fixed_justification: All SonarCloud issues have been addressed, and our release policy ensures any new issues will be identified and quickly addressed.
dynamic_analysis_justification: The OpenCue TSC has decided that this could be useful, but isn't necessary at the moment given the common use cases of OpenCue.
dynamic_analysis_enable_assertions_justi: The OpenCue TSC has decided that this could be useful, but isn't necessary at the moment given the common use cases of OpenCue.
test_continuous_integration_justificatio: GitHub Actions is used to run our CI system. Automated tests are run for all Pull Requests and on our master branch.
discussion_justification: GitHub supports discussions on issues and pull requests.
hardened_site_justification: // X-Content-Type-Options was not set to "nosniff".
implementation_languages: Java, Python, PLSQL, PLpgSQL, Shell, Dockerfile
